9.1 What is Abstraction?

1. Core Principle: Abstraction hides complex implementation details,
                   focusing only on essential features.

2. Focus on Functionality: Emphasizes what an object does, not how it does it,
                           through clear interfaces.

3. Simplifies Complexity: It reduces complexity by showing only
                          relevant information in class design.

4. Real-World Modelling: Abstraction allows creating objects that
                         represent real-life entities with key attributes and behaviours.

